Here is the summary of data of the `show event cpu` requested during the community meeting (05/28) presentation of memory utilization and unmapping info for bgpd and zebra with tcmalloc. The data was collected during testing with 300k routes from 16 ECMP peers advertised to a DUT with 8 cores, 3.855 Ghz cpu and 32G RAM.

The data given here is the execution time of tcmalloc_timer() which runs to monitor the availablity of pageheap_free bytes of a process and releases free bytes back to OS at a configured rate when the pageheap_free bytes goes beyond 20 MB.
We took this data with memory release rate configure to 20 MB/second. 
 
For bgpd, the avg tcmalloc_timer() run time is < 10 micro seconds with a peak of 23.16 ms during peak memory unmapping and it stays < 10 micro seconds during the test durations when there is no unmapping happening.
For zebra, the avg tcmalloc_timer() run time is also < 10 micro seconds and it statys at this level during the entire two iterations of testing (no unmapping happened for zebra)

**tcmalloc_timer() run times**
**_Notes:_** 
- The avg and total times are cumulative times of execution of tcmalloc_timer() over the number of invokations
- The data given here is summary of data observed for one iteration of testing. The data for the second iteration is similar.

